480
00:31:39,520 --> 00:31:41,210
Nothing,except...

481
00:31:41,210 --> 00:31:45,640
I know marco's going to win,I'm going to come second,
and you're going to end up alone with no money.

482
00:31:52,130 --> 00:31:56,500
Don't be jealous.
He's smarter than you,but mom likes you better.

483
00:32:01,690 --> 00:32:04,170
So,uh,who's--
who's smarter than me?

484
00:32:04,170 --> 00:32:06,600
Who knows?

485
00:32:06,600 --> 00:32:09,090
I'm not even sure she knows exactly.

486
00:32:09,090 --> 00:32:11,960
You know,in some ways,
she was better off on the promicin inhibitor.

487
00:32:11,960 --> 00:32:14,410
At least she wasn't overwhelmed
back then.

488
00:32:14,410 --> 00:32:18,730
All she wants to do is record what
she sees in those notebooks.

489
00:32:18,730 --> 00:32:21,790
It's like some kind of compulsion.

490
00:32:23,540 --> 00:32:26,270
Well...
think about it for a minute.

491
00:32:27,370 --> 00:32:31,500
Every morning,she wakes up and...
knows pretty much what's coming.

492
00:32:31,500 --> 00:32:34,170
She's already lived the whole
day once in her head,

493
00:32:34,170 --> 00:32:37,560
and by the time something actually
does happen,it's like a rerun.

494
00:32:37,560 --> 00:32:41,310
- I hate watching reruns.
- Yeah. Try living one.

495
00:32:42,850 --> 00:32:45,060
Hey,what about kevin burkhoff?

496
00:32:45,060 --> 00:32:48,090
Maybe he can figure out a way for
maia to control her visions.

497
00:32:48,090 --> 00:32:49,530
He is brilliant.

498
00:32:49,530 --> 00:32:53,670
I don't say this about many people,
but he is smarter than me.

499
00:32:58,740 --> 00:33:01,720
- I know you.
- Well,of course you do.It's diana skouris.

500
00:33:01,720 --> 00:33:04,320
- You work at ntac.
- I'm not here on business.

501
00:33:04,320 --> 00:33:07,070
I'm here about my daughter maia.

502
00:33:07,070 --> 00:33:09,940
The precog.
What about her?

503
00:33:09,940 --> 00:33:13,190
She's still 10,right?
She's not 65 now,is she?

504
00:33:13,190 --> 00:33:16,860
Interesting guess.
Kind of wide of the mark,though.

505
00:33:16,860 --> 00:33:18,550
Good.

506
00:33:24,360 --> 00:33:26,440
Might as well come on in.

507
00:33:26,930 --> 00:33:29,120
Thank you.

508
00:33:30,070 --> 00:33:32,030
- Oh,sorry about the clutter.
- That's all right.

509
00:33:32,030 --> 00:33:35,500
I fired the maid last week.
She was always cleaning.

510
00:33:41,260 --> 00:33:43,040
Excuse me.

511
00:33:46,330 --> 00:33:48,000
So...

512
00:33:48,920 --> 00:33:50,910
your daughter.

513
00:33:51,900 --> 00:33:54,020
What's troubling her?

514
00:33:55,710 --> 00:33:58,080
OCTOBER 15

515
00:34:58,060 --> 00:35:00,360
I'll let you do it.

516
00:35:00,360 --> 00:35:02,580
I caused all this,right?

517
00:35:02,580 --> 00:35:05,210
And getting rid of me is the only way
to save my mother.

518
00:35:05,210 --> 00:35:07,250
- No...
- that's what you were thinking,wasn't it?

519
00:35:08,240 --> 00:35:09,920
No,it wasn'T.

520
00:35:09,920 --> 00:35:13,120
I don't want her to die either,
so I'll let you do it.I'll...

521
00:35:13,120 --> 00:35:15,930
- I'll even shut my eyes.
- Isabelle...

522
00:35:16,660 --> 00:35:18,850
I would never hurt you.

523
00:35:19,920 --> 00:35:21,940
Why?

524
00:35:22,420 --> 00:35:24,510
I don't understand.
It's the only way to save her.

525
00:35:24,510 --> 00:35:28,020
We don't know that,and I won't
make a choice between the two of you.

526
00:35:28,460 --> 00:35:30,940
"Won't" or "can't"?

527
00:35:44,030 --> 00:35:47,070
Sorry.
I don't mean to invade anyone's space.

528
00:35:47,070 --> 00:35:49,910
Oh,that's okay.
It's not my desk.

529
00:35:50,880 --> 00:35:53,490
But it looks like you'll be here for
a while now,huh?

530
00:35:53,490 --> 00:35:56,400
Assuming this place is still standing
on october 20th,yeah.

531
00:35:56,400 --> 00:36:00,360
Maybe we should talk to jarvis.
Get you a room of your very own.

532
00:36:00,360 --> 00:36:02,430
That's fine with me.

533
00:36:03,150 --> 00:36:06,470
To tell you the truth,I could use a
little bit of a buffer zone.

534
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:11,230
This problem you're having with your daughter'S...

535
00:36:11,230 --> 00:36:13,860
precog ability?

536
00:36:13,860 --> 00:36:18,100
I keep wanting to give you my opinion,
but I don't want to intrude.

537
00:36:18,100 --> 00:36:20,160
So you are...

538
00:36:20,160 --> 00:36:22,210
listening to my thoughts.

539
00:36:22,210 --> 00:36:25,300
You and baldwin.
I can't help it.

540
00:36:25,860 --> 00:36:30,050
I try to tune you guys out,but every now
and then,something leaks through.

541
00:36:30,050 --> 00:36:32,850
I'll try to keep that in mind.

542
00:36:35,910 --> 00:36:39,400
You said you had an opinion about maia.
What is it?

543
00:36:39,820 --> 00:36:41,770
When I first...

544
00:36:42,250 --> 00:36:46,840
developed this thing of mine,
I was a basket case.You saw me.

545
00:36:46,840 --> 00:36:52,210
I truly thought i was going insane,
so I fought against it,

546
00:36:52,610 --> 00:36:54,720
and that just made it worse.

547
00:36:54,720 --> 00:36:58,260
I had to give in to it,
let it take control of me,

548
00:36:58,520 --> 00:37:02,960
and then,slowly,I learned how to
take control of it.

549
00:37:03,640 --> 00:37:06,020
Listen,your kid stops fighting,
and eventually,

550
00:37:06,020 --> 00:37:10,560
it'll become like seeing or hearing
or any other sense.

551
00:37:10,560 --> 00:37:13,440
She won't even think about it.

552
00:37:13,440 --> 00:37:16,260
It's just a part of who she is.

553
00:37:18,390 --> 00:37:21,500
That's how it worked for me,anyway.

554
00:37:23,990 --> 00:37:26,160
Thank you.

555
00:37:26,160 --> 00:37:29,400
Diana.We just got a call from the seattle
police.Someone down there read our apb.

556
00:37:29,400 --> 00:37:31,870
They know exactly where hauser is.

557
00:37:35,250 --> 00:37:36,890
You guys are lucky,actually.

558
00:37:36,890 --> 00:37:40,320
In another day or two,we would have
buried him in potter's field.

559
00:37:40,320 --> 00:37:42,800
- Buried who?
- Him.

560
00:37:42,800 --> 00:37:46,980
I always read the apb memos when they
circulate in the police department.

561
00:37:46,980 --> 00:37:50,330
Kind of a hobby.
Gets boring in here.

562
00:37:50,700 --> 00:37:54,380
Anyway,there was a description of a
regimental tattoo on the memo for hauser.

563
00:37:54,380 --> 00:37:57,000
82nd airborne.
"Death from above."

564
00:37:57,000 --> 00:38:00,170
I remember it from a john doe they
brought in here three weeks ago.

565
00:38:00,170 --> 00:38:01,890
This guy drowned in the harbor.

566
00:38:01,890 --> 00:38:04,240
A lot of veterans have that tattoo.

567
00:38:04,240 --> 00:38:07,900
Do a lot of veterans look exactly
like the mug shot you circulated?

568
00:38:08,440 --> 00:38:11,240
Don't believe me?
Take a look for yourselves.

569
00:38:13,950 --> 00:38:16,670
Say hello to wesley hauser.

570
00:38:19,870 --> 00:38:22,310
Hauser died two and a half weeks
before ryland was attacked.

571
00:38:22,310 --> 00:38:24,320
Obviously,that wasn't him on the
phone the other day.

572
00:38:24,320 --> 00:38:28,370
And that copy of the 4400 report
with all his notes over it?

573
00:38:28,370 --> 00:38:31,010
For all we know,that could have been a plant.

574
00:38:31,010 --> 00:38:32,490
Somebody wanted us distracted.

575
00:38:32,490 --> 00:38:36,100
They deliberately put us on the trail
of some phantom member of the nova group.

576
00:38:36,100 --> 00:38:37,840
I mean,how did we first find out about hauser?

577
00:38:37,840 --> 00:38:39,960
T.J.'S old boyfriend.
He gave us the address.

578
00:38:39,960 --> 00:38:42,300
No,he was thinking it.

579
00:38:43,480 --> 00:38:45,010
At least,according to gary,he was.

580
00:38:45,010 --> 00:38:48,840
Gary navarro put us onto wesley hauser.

581
00:39:09,250 --> 00:39:10,900
Get in.

582
00:39:17,650 --> 00:39:19,770
You lied to me,daniel.

583
00:39:19,770 --> 00:39:21,980
You never said anything about killing people.

584
00:39:21,980 --> 00:39:24,430
We were protecting you,shawn.

585
00:39:24,430 --> 00:39:27,160
If we tell you in advance,you're culpable.

586
00:39:32,860 --> 00:39:35,550
- What is she dohere?
- She's dying.She needs your help.

587
00:39:35,550 --> 00:39:38,780
I told you,I don't want anything more
to do with you.

588
00:39:38,780 --> 00:39:42,390
The nova group was supposed to protect us.
That's why I gave you money,daniel.

589
00:39:42,390 --> 00:39:45,480
That's why I gave you money.
Not to start a terrorist organization!

590
00:39:45,480 --> 00:39:49,340
We'll talk about your concerns later.
She's got a stomach wound,and it's infected.

591
00:39:49,340 --> 00:39:52,240
She needs you right now,
or she's not going to make it.

592
00:39:52,240 --> 00:39:55,120
Shawn,she's a 4400.

593
00:39:55,120 --> 00:39:58,590
If we don't help each other,
what hope do we have?

594
00:40:02,930 --> 00:40:04,900
Give me your hand.

595
00:41:31,430 --> 00:41:33,480
What are you doing here?

596
00:41:34,150 --> 00:41:36,390
You're awake.
Good.

597
00:41:38,610 --> 00:41:41,530
It's important that you know it was me.

598
00:41:46,540 --> 00:41:48,990
I'm the guy who killed you.

599
00:42:12,170 --> 00:42:14,900
Med post.
Do you have a 20 on gary navarro?

600
00:42:14,900 --> 00:42:17,860
Yeah,he just walked by.
Why?

601
00:42:17,860 --> 00:42:20,410
- Get him!
- Hey! Stop!

602
00:42:20,410 --> 00:42:22,750
Go. I'll check on ryland.

603
00:42:24,280 --> 00:42:26,440
He's seizing.
He's bradying down.

604
00:42:26,440 --> 00:42:29,340
I need a crash cart and ativan.
Find dr. Danoff.

605
00:42:29,340 --> 00:42:31,100
Now!

606
00:42:38,100 --> 00:42:40,750
Stay right there,gary.

607
00:42:46,190 --> 00:42:48,690
Isabelle.
Isabelle!

608
00:42:48,690 --> 00:42:52,160
Oh,god.
Somebody call an ambulance!

609
00:42:53,470 --> 00:42:56,370
What's everybody standing around for?
Somebody call an ambulance!

610
00:42:56,370 --> 00:42:59,590
They're on their way!

611
00:43:02,790 --> 00:43:05,170
- Somebody call an ambulance--
- dad...

612
00:43:20,080 --> 00:43:22,090
what am I?

613
00:43:23,850 --> 00:43:26,180
It's miraculous,shawn.

614
00:43:26,810 --> 00:43:29,290
I watch you heal someone,and...

615
00:43:29,290 --> 00:43:32,560
it makes me wonder why they
hate us so much.

616
00:43:33,150 --> 00:43:35,750
They hate us because you're killing them,
daniel.

617
00:43:35,750 --> 00:43:38,680
They're afraid of us.
I can't blame them.

618
00:43:39,510 --> 00:43:43,180
You make it sound like we acted out of
some sort of blood lust.

619
00:43:44,620 --> 00:43:47,860
These were precise,tactical strikes,shawn,

620
00:43:47,860 --> 00:43:52,030
and you and every other 4400 are
ultimately much safer because of them.

621
00:43:52,030 --> 00:43:55,960
You killed people.That's not what we discussed
when you approached me.

622
00:43:55,960 --> 00:43:58,600
I gave you money to start a defensive
arm for the center in case

623
00:43:58,600 --> 00:44:00,550
the government ever came after us again.

624
00:44:00,550 --> 00:44:01,790
It was a precaution.

625
00:44:01,790 --> 00:44:04,230
And all we've done is taken
precautionary measures.

626
00:44:04,230 --> 00:44:06,280
Shawn,do you think that because
their inhibitor program

627
00:44:06,280 --> 00:44:09,110
was exposed that the government's
just going to leave us in peace?

628
00:44:09,110 --> 00:44:12,610
No,they know we've gotten stronger,
which threatens their hold on power,

629
00:44:12,610 --> 00:44:14,730
which increases their need to eliminate us.

630
00:44:14,730 --> 00:44:16,840
So we strike first?

631
00:44:17,510 --> 00:44:19,550
Is that it?

632
00:44:20,290 --> 00:44:22,400
Is that what happens on the 19th?

633
00:44:22,400 --> 00:44:27,090
Look,shawn,you do great work at
that center of yours.

634
00:44:27,090 --> 00:44:32,240
You just focus on that.I don't want to
distract you.Knowledge can be a burden.

635
00:44:34,940 --> 00:44:37,250
And thanks for helping T.J. Out.

636
00:44:37,250 --> 00:44:40,770
You're a hero to your own people.
Never forget that.

637
00:44:44,710 --> 00:44:46,380
Yeah.

638
00:44:49,470 --> 00:44:51,210
It did not work,you know.

639
00:44:51,210 --> 00:44:54,350
Ryland was O.D.'Ing,
but the doctors pulled him out of it.

640
00:44:54,350 --> 00:44:56,310
He'll be awake within a couple of hours.

641
00:44:56,310 --> 00:44:59,580
Well,I'm sure you're as
disappointed as I am.

642
00:44:59,580 --> 00:45:02,110
Don't worry.
We'll get him.

643
00:45:02,110 --> 00:45:05,530
Let's talk about wesley hauser.
You first met him in quarantine.

644
00:45:07,000 --> 00:45:08,360
I liked wes.

645
00:45:08,360 --> 00:45:11,210
He was 10 kinds of crazy,but his heart
was in the right place.

646
00:45:11,210 --> 00:45:14,770
I guess he was bipolar or something,
but he never took medication.

647
00:45:14,770 --> 00:45:17,940
After quarantine,he lived on the streets.

648
00:45:17,940 --> 00:45:21,720
I used to visit him down at the docks.
You know,give him food,a little money.

649
00:45:21,720 --> 00:45:23,550
So when did you decide to kill him?

650
00:45:23,550 --> 00:45:26,990
Wes,he didn't need my help with that.

651
00:45:26,990 --> 00:45:29,740
He drank about three bottles of mad dog a day.

652
00:45:29,740 --> 00:45:33,310
One morning about a month ago,
I went down to see him,and...

653
00:45:35,380 --> 00:45:37,710
I found him by the dumpster.

654
00:45:37,710 --> 00:45:38,670
Dead.

655
00:45:38,670 --> 00:45:42,470
And somewhere in the middle of your grieving
process,you figured he'd make a handy decoy.

656
00:45:42,470 --> 00:45:44,260
Hauser wouldn't have minded.

657
00:45:44,260 --> 00:45:47,430
XXXXXXXX Going back to his marine corps days.

658
00:45:47,850 --> 00:45:51,840
So when I found him,I said a word
or two over his body,

659
00:45:53,370 --> 00:45:54,910
and I pushed him into elliott bay.

660
00:45:54,910 --> 00:45:57,200
So how long have you been working
with this nova group?

661
00:45:57,200 --> 00:45:59,420
Did someone approach you,or was the
whole thing your idea?

662
00:45:59,420 --> 00:46:02,830
Tell me...
you and this girlfriend of yours...

663
00:46:03,230 --> 00:46:06,280
is it like a role-playing thing you get up to?

664
00:46:06,280 --> 00:46:08,870
Or is she actually taking you into these...

665
00:46:08,870 --> 00:46:12,190
I don't know.What do you call it?
Fantasy worlds?

666
00:46:13,240 --> 00:46:15,910
Oh,and this guy marco...

667
00:46:15,910 --> 00:46:18,970
does he know that you're too...

668
00:46:19,720 --> 00:46:23,140
embarrassed to tell your partner
that you two have been dating?

669
00:46:24,390 --> 00:46:26,830
Done showing off?

670
00:46:26,830 --> 00:46:29,810
Why don't you tell us what's
going to happen on october 19th?

671
00:46:29,810 --> 00:46:33,090
I guess you're going to have
to find yourself another telepath.

672
00:46:38,530 --> 00:46:41,190
Good luck with that.

673
00:46:41,190 --> 00:46:42,460
So you got nothing out of him?

674
00:46:42,460 --> 00:46:46,440
Well,he told us about hauser,but as far as the
nova goes,it's going to take time to break him down.

675
00:46:46,440 --> 00:46:49,350
- How much time?
- He's a telepath.He knows what we're thinking.

676
00:46:49,350 --> 00:46:51,700
- A little longer than usual.
- Okay,so it's not easy,

677
00:46:51,700 --> 00:46:54,680
but gary navarro has a level-seven
security clearance.

678
00:46:54,680 --> 00:46:58,000
We have to assume that he's been using it to
funnel national secrets to the nova group.

679
00:46:58,000 --> 00:47:00,380
We need to know what he knows.
Now.

680
00:47:00,380 --> 00:47:02,270
He'll talk.

681
00:47:02,270 --> 00:47:06,100
Gary's been inside our heads for a year.
I think I know how to get inside of his.

682
00:47:10,610 --> 00:47:11,840
Careful with this.

683
00:47:11,840 --> 00:47:13,470
Matthew.

684
00:47:15,300 --> 00:47:17,590
I didn't expect to see you back
for a couple of weeks.

685
00:47:17,590 --> 00:47:20,220
The nova group revised my calendar for me.

686
00:47:20,540 --> 00:47:22,850
Wiped it clean,actually.

687
00:47:22,850 --> 00:47:25,060
It's difficult to lobby on behalf of the 4400

688
00:47:25,060 --> 00:47:27,710
when some of them are boasting about
their body count.

689
00:47:27,710 --> 00:47:28,940
I suppose.

690
00:47:28,940 --> 00:47:31,210
How's lily?
Any improvement since I left?

691
00:47:31,210 --> 00:47:34,530
- If anything,she's getting worse.
- Sorry to hear that.

692
00:47:34,950 --> 00:47:36,520
Isabelle?

693
00:47:36,520 --> 00:47:39,340
She tried to kill herself this morning.

694
00:47:40,190 --> 00:47:42,460
She jumped off the roof.

695
00:47:42,460 --> 00:47:45,530
A few minutes later,she was walking
around like nothing happened.

696
00:47:45,530 --> 00:47:47,250
I got to tell you,matthew...
I'm not going to lie.

697
00:47:47,250 --> 00:47:50,260
I'm really glad you're back.

698
00:48:12,780 --> 00:48:14,730
Hello,isabelle.

699
00:48:15,850 --> 00:48:18,630
Hello. Who are you?

700
00:48:19,120 --> 00:48:21,220
My name is matthew ross.

701
00:48:21,220 --> 00:48:23,320
I work closely with shawn.

702
00:48:23,320 --> 00:48:26,910
I'm an advisor to the 4400.
May I come in?

703
00:48:35,860 --> 00:48:38,940
I understand there was an incident
this morning.

704
00:48:39,760 --> 00:48:42,830
You attempted...
to harm yourself.

705
00:48:45,440 --> 00:48:47,360
I see.

706
00:48:50,020 --> 00:48:52,060
You had no right to do that!

707
00:48:52,060 --> 00:48:55,690
Don't you understand who you are?
What you're here to do?

708
00:48:56,400 --> 00:48:58,200
- No...
- well,I do.

709
00:48:58,200 --> 00:48:59,460
I know everything about you,isabelle.

710
00:48:59,460 --> 00:49:02,530
I know why you're here,and I know what
you're supposed to do.

711
00:49:03,970 --> 00:49:05,510
Sit...

712
00:49:05,510 --> 00:49:07,790
and I'll tell you a story.

713
00:49:08,810 --> 00:49:10,220
You'll like it.

714
00:49:10,220 --> 00:49:14,030
It's about your past,and it's about your future.

715
00:49:18,550 --> 00:49:21,030
I know you went to a lot of
trouble to get this.

716
00:49:21,030 --> 00:49:23,030
Thank you.
But?

717
00:49:23,030 --> 00:49:26,970
I'm not sure i want to send maia
to a school that only teaches 4400s.

718
00:49:26,970 --> 00:49:30,790
It sounds like a great way to get
her to withdraw even further from the world.

719
00:49:31,540 --> 00:49:32,870
Look,just...

720
00:49:32,870 --> 00:49:35,470
just pretend it's got nothing to
do with the 4400 for a second.

721
00:49:35,470 --> 00:49:37,160
It's a good school.

722
00:49:37,160 --> 00:49:41,150
You know,top-notch faculty,
the facilities are great,and it's all free.

723
00:49:41,150 --> 00:49:43,700
The 4400 center picks up the whole tab.

724
00:49:43,950 --> 00:49:46,730
They even have a class on how
to manage your abilities.

725
00:49:46,730 --> 00:49:50,030
Just give me some time to think about it,okay?
It's a big step.

726
00:49:51,810 --> 00:49:54,000
I was king of hoping dr.
Burkhoff would have...

727
00:49:54,000 --> 00:49:56,850
I don't know,a magic pill or something.

728
00:49:56,850 --> 00:49:59,690
What's he working on?
Anything interesting?

729
00:50:00,570 --> 00:50:04,980
You know that promicin serum that
he invented that saved everybody?

730
00:50:04,980 --> 00:50:09,560
Well,I saw a syringe at his place,
and it looked like there was some in it.

731
00:50:09,560 --> 00:50:11,500
Well,he's a researcher,right?

732
00:50:11,500 --> 00:50:14,140
He's probably injecting it into,
what,mice,guinea pigs?

733
00:50:14,140 --> 00:50:17,360
The only animals i saw at his place
were a couple of cockroaches.

734
00:50:17,360 --> 00:50:20,870
You don't think he's injecting it
into himself,do you?

735
00:50:20,870 --> 00:50:25,610
That's ridiculous.I am not injecting
myself with the promicin serum.

736
00:50:25,610 --> 00:50:27,710
Good.
I'm glad to hear it.

737
00:50:27,710 --> 00:50:32,720
I'm injecting myself with a modified
version of the promicin serum.

738
00:50:33,680 --> 00:50:36,530
Dr. Burkhoff,I have to ask you this.

739
00:50:37,650 --> 00:50:39,120
Have you stopped taking your medication?

740
00:50:39,120 --> 00:50:41,950
Of course not.
I'm as sane as you are.

741
00:50:44,730 --> 00:50:47,710
Once the course of treatment is finished,

742
00:50:47,710 --> 00:50:51,900
I will have taught my body how
to produce promicin,

743
00:50:51,900 --> 00:50:57,330
and then I will be the first
non-returnee to develop 4400 abilities.

744
00:50:57,330 --> 00:50:59,760
The first of many.

745
00:50:59,760 --> 00:51:02,870
You're talking about the next
step in human evolution.

746
00:51:03,210 --> 00:51:06,120
- Do you think the world is ready for that?
- The world is never ready for change.

747
00:51:06,120 --> 00:51:10,340
You have to force it on them.
Isn't that why the 4400 were brought back?

748
00:51:10,340 --> 00:51:14,300
Isn't that why the future woke me up?

749
00:51:15,320 --> 00:51:20,640
You shouldn't be doing research
of this magnitude in--excuse me,but...

750
00:51:21,050 --> 00:51:22,110
in a dump.

751
00:51:22,110 --> 00:51:25,110
These are hardly sterile working conditions.

752
00:51:25,110 --> 00:51:28,730
You could help me with that.
You have scientific background,right?

753
00:51:28,730 --> 00:51:31,790
I have graduate degrees in microbiology
and epidemiology.

754
00:51:31,790 --> 00:51:33,250
Good.

755
00:51:33,250 --> 00:51:35,060
That'll be handy.

756
00:51:35,060 --> 00:51:37,870
I need someone to monitor my progress...

757
00:51:37,870 --> 00:51:40,010
as the changes...

758
00:51:40,720 --> 00:51:42,410
continue.

759
00:51:42,920 --> 00:51:44,950
Changes?

760
00:51:50,780 --> 00:51:54,070
I think it's an exciting first step.
Don't you?

761
00:51:57,690 --> 00:52:01,680
I was thinking,next time,we could make a
world where kyle never shot jordan collier,

762
00:52:01,680 --> 00:52:05,720
never went to prison,the inhibitor
scandal never happened...

763
00:52:05,720 --> 00:52:07,640
sounds nice...

764
00:52:07,640 --> 00:52:09,250
although i have to tell you,at the moment,

765
00:52:09,250 --> 00:52:13,290
I'm not really feeling the need to be
transported to some kind of fantasy world.

766
00:52:13,930 --> 00:52:19,440
As long as this water stays hot,things
are a-okay with me right here in reality.

767
00:52:20,510 --> 00:52:22,690
Maybe tomorrow we can try it again.

768
00:52:22,690 --> 00:52:24,200
I'll take a rain check.

769
00:52:24,200 --> 00:52:28,730
I'm going to a seminar at
the 4400 center tomorrow.

770
00:52:31,080 --> 00:52:34,670
It's about what we can expect
physically now that we're off the inhibitor.

771
00:52:34,670 --> 00:52:37,780
Is everything okay?
I mean,you're not having any problems,are you?

772
00:52:37,780 --> 00:52:41,800
No,I feel fine.
I feel great,actually.

773
00:52:42,840 --> 00:52:45,750
Well,then I don't get it.
Why do you need to go?

774
00:52:45,750 --> 00:52:49,660
I don'T.I want to go.
I'm curious.

775
00:52:50,020 --> 00:52:51,720
But alana,you never...

776
00:52:51,720 --> 00:52:54,780
you never wanted to go to the center before.
Why start now?

777
00:52:54,780 --> 00:52:59,030
I never felt the need to be around
other 4400s before.

778
00:52:59,740 --> 00:53:01,540
Now you do?

779
00:53:02,220 --> 00:53:05,460
It's just a seminar,thomas.

780
00:53:06,220 --> 00:53:08,750
Yeah,okay.

781
00:53:09,320 --> 00:53:11,370
I get it.

782
00:53:12,050 --> 00:53:14,030
OCTOBER 16

783
00:53:18,830 --> 00:53:20,680
Do you recognize those names?

784
00:53:20,680 --> 00:53:23,780
They're 4400s,all of them foreign nationals.

785
00:53:23,780 --> 00:53:27,600
Alessandro ortiz from venezuela.
Ismael namir from libya.

786
00:53:27,600 --> 00:53:30,940
Chitra singh from indonesia.
They've all gone missing in the past year.

787
00:53:30,940 --> 00:53:32,770
That's one year.

788
00:53:32,770 --> 00:53:35,990
Now,that's about as long you've
worked for the nsa,isn't it,gary?

789
00:53:35,990 --> 00:53:41,200
We checked your travel records.
You left venezuela two days before ortiz disappeared.

790
00:53:41,200 --> 00:53:44,440
Same thing in libya,indonesia...
everyone on that list.

791
00:53:44,440 --> 00:53:46,060
You were there,they went away.

792
00:53:46,060 --> 00:53:49,240
What exactly did you do for the nsa,gary?

793
00:53:50,110 --> 00:53:53,620
There's an arms race going on,isn't there?
Only now it's with 4400s.

794
00:53:53,620 --> 00:53:56,490
These people,I bet their abilities
make the wrong people very nervous.

795
00:53:56,490 --> 00:54:00,550
And the nsa couldn't stand by while foreign--
and potentially hostile--

796
00:54:00,550 --> 00:54:04,940
governments developed,what,
human weapons of mass destruction?

797
00:54:04,940 --> 00:54:06,680
Is this list complete?

798
00:54:06,680 --> 00:54:09,050
'Cause I'm just wondering
how many 4400s you did kill.

799
00:54:09,050 --> 00:54:11,480
I did not kill anyone.

800
00:54:11,480 --> 00:54:13,530
Oh,no,no,no,you just got the right
people in the right zip code.

801
00:54:13,530 --> 00:54:15,900
Because you,you were living back home--

802
00:54:16,480 --> 00:54:18,050
what did he say?
Oh,yeah--

803
00:54:18,050 --> 00:54:22,090
"very comfortably" when the actual
dirty work was done.

804
00:54:23,410 --> 00:54:27,240
And that's why you went across to
the nova group,isn't it,gary?

805
00:54:27,240 --> 00:54:30,250
Because you just couldn't live with yourself.

806
00:54:30,250 --> 00:54:35,440
The nsa told me that I was helping my country.

807
00:54:39,300 --> 00:54:41,940
They didn't fill in the blanks.

808
00:54:43,120 --> 00:54:45,580
I had to do that myself.

809
00:54:45,580 --> 00:54:47,200
You felt used.

810
00:54:47,200 --> 00:54:50,580
They made you a weapon against your own people.
So when did you figure it out?

811
00:54:52,440 --> 00:54:54,300
- What's up?
- Who are these guys?

812
00:54:54,300 --> 00:54:57,380
This is agent wood and dr. Boll of the nsa.

813
00:54:57,380 --> 00:55:00,220
They've been brought in to help
expedite the interrogation.

814
00:55:02,350 --> 00:55:04,950
Okay,first of all,no more sitting.

815
00:55:04,950 --> 00:55:07,430
What's going on?
Brought in by who?

816
00:55:07,430 --> 00:55:10,680
Gary navarro tried to kill me.
I made a phone call.

817
00:55:10,680 --> 00:55:12,460
You should be in jail right now,dennis.

818
00:55:12,460 --> 00:55:14,640
I still have a few friends,tom.

819
00:55:14,640 --> 00:55:17,430
I had him talking.
I was making progress.

820
00:55:17,430 --> 00:55:19,130
Not fast enough.

821
00:55:19,130 --> 00:55:21,960
The members of gary's cell
know he's been taken.

822
00:55:21,960 --> 00:55:24,440
They're already changing their plans.

823
00:55:24,440 --> 00:55:28,960
If it takes too long to break him,
the information he gives us is stale.

824
00:55:28,960 --> 00:55:31,480
October 19th is three days away.

825
00:55:31,480 --> 00:55:32,470
Yeah.

826
00:55:32,470 --> 00:55:37,700
I know you find this hard to believe,
tom,but we're on the same side.

827
00:55:37,700 --> 00:55:40,360
We have the same goal.

828
00:55:40,360 --> 00:55:43,200
Those agents are tools.

829
00:55:43,990 --> 00:55:46,180
Use them.

830
00:55:55,560 --> 00:55:57,810
You're sitting in my spot.

831
00:55:58,290 --> 00:56:00,760
- Sorry.
- It's okay.

832
00:56:00,760 --> 00:56:03,500
There's room for two people to sit.

833
00:56:09,590 --> 00:56:12,930
You got stalin,pol pot,and the marquis de sade?

834
00:56:13,940 --> 00:56:15,750
Did you finish all the fun books?

835
00:56:15,750 --> 00:56:17,890
Well,I'm interested in learning
more about evil.

836
00:56:17,890 --> 00:56:20,330
Everybody's scared of me,so I thought,

837
00:56:20,330 --> 00:56:24,000
"what if they're right?What if I'm bad?"

838
00:56:24,000 --> 00:56:25,970
Why would you think that?

839
00:56:26,650 --> 00:56:29,310
Sometimes I think i feel it inside of me,
like....

840
00:56:29,620 --> 00:56:32,050
I could be capable of anything.

841
00:56:32,050 --> 00:56:34,440
Everyone's capable of anything.

842
00:56:34,880 --> 00:56:37,110
- Believe me,I know.
- How?

843
00:56:37,460 --> 00:56:40,560
- Have you done bad things?
- Yeah,of course I have.

844
00:56:40,560 --> 00:56:42,890
Will you tell me about them?

845
00:56:43,630 --> 00:56:45,370
Um,okay.

846
00:56:46,820 --> 00:56:49,980
- I slept with my brother's girlfriend.
- How bad is that?

847
00:56:49,980 --> 00:56:52,950
Some people would call that a major betrayal.

848
00:56:52,950 --> 00:56:55,210
A lot of hard feelings.

849
00:56:56,030 --> 00:56:57,660
This man did much worse than that.

850
00:56:57,660 --> 00:57:01,090
Well,I'm not a dictator,but

851
00:57:01,090 --> 00:57:03,320
I've done the big kind of bad,too.

852
00:57:03,320 --> 00:57:07,420
I can't say much about it,
but I gave some money to some people.

853
00:57:07,420 --> 00:57:10,750
They used it for something really,
really wrong,and...

854
00:57:11,150 --> 00:57:13,950
- I don't think that they're finished.
- Well,can you stop them?

855
00:57:13,950 --> 00:57:17,740
I could turn them in,but the thing is
so far,they've only gone after bad people,

856
00:57:17,740 --> 00:57:20,510
people that tried to kill me,
tried to kill all of us.

857
00:57:20,510 --> 00:57:24,510
So if they've only gone after bad people,
then doesn't that make them good?

858
00:57:24,870 --> 00:57:26,650
Maybe.

859
00:57:27,030 --> 00:57:28,760
I don't know.

860
00:57:38,840 --> 00:57:41,190
We're relating now,aren't we?

861
00:57:41,450 --> 00:57:43,970
I read about this.

862
00:57:45,310 --> 00:57:47,350
Yeah,we are.

863
00:57:52,210 --> 00:57:54,460
How was it for you?

864
00:57:54,460 --> 00:57:56,700
I liked it.

865
00:57:57,650 --> 00:57:59,700
We talked.

866
00:58:00,130 --> 00:58:02,160
It helped me understand good and evil.

867
00:58:02,160 --> 00:58:06,200
According to you,you get to pick.
It's a choice.

868
00:58:07,600 --> 00:58:10,260
I have it right,don't I?

869
00:58:13,220 --> 00:58:15,580
Yeah,you do.

870
00:58:18,080 --> 00:58:19,960
OCTOBER 17

871
00:58:21,630 --> 00:58:23,420
I can't open my hand.

872
00:58:23,420 --> 00:58:27,150
I woke up from a nap,
and it was all bunched up like this.

873
00:58:27,150 --> 00:58:29,870
Arthritis I can handle.

874
00:58:47,840 --> 00:58:50,130
That feels good.

875
00:58:58,440 --> 00:59:01,200
You're like a human heating pad.

876
00:59:02,870 --> 00:59:04,260
I like that.

877
00:59:04,260 --> 00:59:06,930
Human heating pad.
I'll take it as a compliment.

878
00:59:07,370 --> 00:59:09,500
Seriously,you better?

879
00:59:10,020 --> 00:59:12,050
Yeah.

880
00:59:16,300 --> 00:59:19,570
I've been trading emails with
somebody down at the mayo clinic.

881
00:59:19,570 --> 00:59:23,380
He says we should go to sweden
and try this experimental treatment.

882
00:59:24,330 --> 00:59:25,920
Here.

883
00:59:26,590 --> 00:59:28,200
What's this?

884
00:59:28,200 --> 00:59:30,450
Open it.

885
00:59:38,150 --> 00:59:41,700
Can you believe that the air
force lets you do that now?

886
00:59:41,700 --> 00:59:46,070
You give them some money,
and they let you ride along in an f-16.

887
00:59:46,540 --> 00:59:48,270
It says here i get to take the controls.

888
00:59:48,270 --> 00:59:50,610
Oh,I talked to the guy who was
in charge of the program,

889
00:59:50,610 --> 00:59:53,330
and I told him about your
background as a pilot,

890
00:59:53,330 --> 00:59:57,330
and he said he would let you
drive for 30 seconds.

891
00:59:57,330 --> 00:59:59,630
Lily,I was a pilot in 1950.

892
00:59:59,630 --> 01:00:02,090
That's why it's only 30 seconds.

893
01:00:04,020 --> 01:00:06,100
Happy birthday,richard.

894
01:00:06,100 --> 01:00:09,440
Thanks,but it's not my birthday
for another six weeks.

895
01:00:10,720 --> 01:00:14,060
Richard,I'm not going to be
here in six weeks.

896
01:00:15,650 --> 01:00:17,460
That's not true.

897
01:00:17,460 --> 01:00:21,140
Yes,it is.
You and I have both known for a while.

898
01:00:22,900 --> 01:00:25,510
Richard,I'm dying.

899
01:00:25,870 --> 01:00:27,350
Lily...

900
01:00:27,350 --> 01:00:31,110
I know how hard this is on you,
but you can't give up.

901
01:00:31,470 --> 01:00:34,580
Shawn said he's willing to stay
here with you all day if he has to.

902
01:00:34,580 --> 01:00:36,480
He'll keep you healthy.

903
01:00:36,480 --> 01:00:38,840
He can'T.

904
01:00:38,840 --> 01:00:42,380
Not anymore.

905
01:00:53,960 --> 01:00:56,350
Are all these people 4400s?

906
01:00:56,350 --> 01:00:58,970
Well,some are,and some just wish they were.

907
01:00:58,970 --> 01:01:01,110
Why would they want that?

908
01:01:02,390 --> 01:01:04,590
Good morning.
Welcome to the center.

909
01:01:04,590 --> 01:01:06,480
Are you a 4400?

910
01:01:06,480 --> 01:01:08,880
No,sweetie.
Are you?

911
01:01:11,100 --> 01:01:14,780
Well,it is an honor to meet you.
Are you here to take our seminar?

912
01:01:14,780 --> 01:01:16,390
No,we're here to look at the school.

913
01:01:16,390 --> 01:01:18,600
We have an appointment with ms. Tobey.

914
01:01:18,600 --> 01:01:20,520
I'll get her right away.

915
01:01:20,520 --> 01:01:23,940
In the meantime,would you sign
in and register your ability?

916
01:01:23,940 --> 01:01:26,520
We're creating a database.

917
01:01:31,920 --> 01:01:34,290
You sure you want to do this?

918
01:01:34,730 --> 01:01:37,240
I want to meet kids like me.

919
01:01:39,270 --> 01:01:41,870
My name is alana mareva.

920
01:01:42,410 --> 01:01:45,500
I have to admit,

921
01:01:45,500 --> 01:01:48,710
I was pretty hesitant about
coming here today.

922
01:01:49,800 --> 01:01:54,330
I was lucky.My life was pretty
much intact when I was returned.

923
01:01:56,850 --> 01:01:59,580
I never thought much about being a 4400,

924
01:02:01,180 --> 01:02:04,480
but when we all got sick,

925
01:02:04,480 --> 01:02:08,180
and seeing everyone together in quarantine...

926
01:02:10,240 --> 01:02:14,280
it made me feel like I had been
denying a part of myself,

927
01:02:14,280 --> 01:02:16,270
so...

928
01:02:16,270 --> 01:02:20,050
here I am,and I'm glad I came.

929
01:02:34,150 --> 01:02:35,960
Anything you want to tell me?

930
01:02:41,800 --> 01:02:43,340
Gary...

931
01:02:46,200 --> 01:02:48,180
Let's end this.

932
01:02:49,670 --> 01:02:51,900
I'll let you sit down.

933
01:02:52,800 --> 01:02:55,350
Who contacted you first?

934
01:02:55,350 --> 01:02:57,780
Just give me a name.

935
01:02:59,560 --> 01:03:01,590
Oh,man.

936
01:03:13,240 --> 01:03:15,370
So how about it?

937
01:03:16,680 --> 01:03:19,960
October 19th is two days away.

938
01:03:20,470 --> 01:03:23,320
Now,you got something to tell me or not?

939
01:03:24,710 --> 01:03:26,920
Suit yourself.

940
01:03:31,040 --> 01:03:34,980
One of our members has been compromised.
I have to assume he's going to give up my name.

941
01:03:34,980 --> 01:03:38,550
So you call me?
For all I know,ntac is monitoring this line.

942
01:03:38,550 --> 01:03:41,790
Well,we're going to have to go underground.
It's going to cost money.

943
01:03:41,790 --> 01:03:43,400
You think I'm just going to
write you a check?

944
01:03:43,400 --> 01:03:46,290
You can arrange it however you want.
I need it tomorrow.

945
01:03:46,290 --> 01:03:49,450
I will see you at the usual
spot at the usual time.

946
01:03:49,450 --> 01:03:53,040
We are in a war,
and we all have to do our part.

947
01:04:09,080 --> 01:04:11,990
Talk to me,gary.
What do you got to say,man?

948
01:04:12,640 --> 01:04:15,100
Talk to me!
Talk to me,gary.

949
01:04:18,270 --> 01:04:20,380
I need names.

950
01:04:23,300 --> 01:04:25,680
Give me a name!

951
01:04:31,770 --> 01:04:34,830
- Talk to me,gary.
- Daniel armand!

952
01:04:35,720 --> 01:04:38,090
Daniel armand.

953
01:04:38,870 --> 01:04:41,120
Daniel armand.

954
01:04:42,780 --> 01:04:44,400
Okay.

955
01:04:44,400 --> 01:04:46,040
It's a start.

956
01:04:46,040 --> 01:04:49,440
- Who else?
- That's it. He was my only contact.

957
01:04:51,080 --> 01:04:55,260
I never met anyone else in the group.
He kept us all separate.

958
01:04:55,260 --> 01:04:58,470
I'm sorry.I'm just having a hard
time believing that's true.

959
01:04:58,470 --> 01:05:01,590
His pulse is tachy at 210.
Systolic's up to 240.

960
01:05:01,590 --> 01:05:02,820
We need to lay off.

961
01:05:02,820 --> 01:05:05,750
- We've only got one name.
